column5: After a decent weekend last week, couldn't wait to get back out today. Arrived at the stream in darkness.  After gearing up and having a quick beverage we hit the river.  I had my first 3lb hen in before the other two gents even had their lines tied up.  And they wonder why I tie up the night before.  In total today I went 3 for 5 due to a few breakoffs...       Tight lines!
Thats a real beauty man, looking forward to this week!
for sure dude. i have some drywalling/painting to do this week, but maybe we can sneak away on wednesday. i'll put you on to a chromer.

Wow congrats! i was fishin some superior tribs yesterday and didnt even see any steel! i had a few missed hits. and got a few brookies on a cleo but that was it! i had to go back to the rapids today to make sure i still had it haha got to hens around 7 lbs... but those superior steelhead still seem to elude me haha
Nice. I missed 3 today at the powerhouse tailrace and watched another board member net one. It was my aniversary so I couldn't stay too long,,,but at least I got out. Trying again tomorrow
Dr S nice work again.... Beauty bows man.... Dara I may see you out there again today...   TDunn

here's a video with music of the fight.  i posted it yesterday on youtube, but the quality after conversion was terrible.  i'm going to post my videos on vimeo instead.  check it out if you have 5 minutes.  cheers!  http://www.vimeo.com/7756313
Way to go. I can now say I know what that feels like.  Awesome!

Pretty nice Luc. Seems like your buddy should be paying attention to what is successful.  That 10mins of prep the night before make is difficult eh?   I like the vid and pics, keep it up.   Also can't believe how high it is....like a foot or more from last fall. Might have to head down there at christmas, could be interesting to get out though.
